rComments: Shai Cohen is an amazing professor. He's passionate about teaching and tells the most interesting stories ever. He makes everything crystal clear by going through alot of examples in class. I wasn't even registered in his class but still went, his lectures are pretty fun if you don't hate math. He's very helpful. Sometimes explains other subjects.

He taught well and most could be found in the textbook. He anwsered all the questions we asked in class and during office hours. However, his tests were really hard, many people failed the first test and the highest was 79%, but overall a good prof.
